      "source": [
        "# Exercise A: activation function behavior\n",
        "\n",
        "Activation choices strongly shape optimization [@Goodfellow.Bengio.Courville.2016]."
      ],
      "id": "a82f40bf"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = np.linspace(-8, 8, 500)\n",
        "\n",
        "sigmoid = 1 / (1 + np.exp(-x))\n",
        "tanh = np.tanh(x)\n",
        "relu = np.maximum(0, x)\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(14, 4))\n",
        "axes[0].plot(x, sigmoid)\n",
        "axes[0].set_title(\"Sigmoid\")\n",
        "axes[1].plot(x, tanh)\n",
        "axes[1].set_title(\"Tanh\")\n",
        "axes[2].plot(x, relu)\n",
        "axes[2].set_title(\"ReLU\")\n",
        "for ax in axes:\n",
        "    ax.grid(alpha=0.25)\n",
        "    ax.set_xlabel(\"x\")\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "95442b6b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Quick interpretation:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Sigmoid and tanh saturate at large magnitudes.\n",
        "2. ReLU is linear on positive inputs and zero on negative inputs.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Exercise B: softmax and confidence"
      ],
      "id": "def64e5a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "logits = torch.tensor([[2.0, 1.0, 0.1], [0.5, 0.5, 0.5], [5.0, 1.0, -2.0]])\n",
        "probs = torch.softmax(logits, dim=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"logits:\\n\", logits)\n",
        "print(\"softmax probabilities:\\n\", probs)\n",
        "print(\"row sums:\", probs.sum(dim=1))"
      ],
      "id": "2f8cdeb0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Discussion:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Higher logit gaps lead to more confident distributions.\n",
        "2. Softmax normalizes each row to sum to 1.\n",
        "\n",
